{"author": null, "tick": "", "link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/main-streets-index-the-betterinvesting-100-increased-115-a-year-for-10-years-through-december-beating-its-sp-benchmark-2018-01-09", "head": "Main Street's Index, the BetterInvesting 100, Increased 11.5% a Year for 10 Years Through December, Beating Its S&P Benchmark - MarketWatch", "text": "Published: MADISON HEIGHTS, Mich., Jan. 9, 2018 /PRNewswire/ -- At the end of December, the BetterInvesting 100 Index (BIXX), reflecting the portfolios of Main Street investors, increased 11.5 percent annually for the previous 10 years, versus annual growth of 10.2 percent for the Standard & Poor's 500 Equal-Weight Index (based on a total return for both indexes in which dividends are reinvested). The BetterInvesting index's five-year gain matched that of the S&P 500 EWI, with annual growth of 15.8 percent. The index increased 1.6 percent from the end of November. BIXX's total return index ended December at 448.78, compared with 441.68 at the end of November. Without dividends reinvested, the index was 338.76 at the end of December, an annual increase of 8.5 percent for the past 10 years and of 13.9 percent for the past five years. The BetterInvesting 100 Index comprises the most popular holdings of investment clubs, employing annual data from the online club accounting program. calculates the index, which began on April 9, 2007, at a base value of 150. BIXX is equal-weighted, meaning that each component constitutes the same percentage in the index. BIXX reflects actual portfolio decisions by individual investors in investment clubs, while other indexes are weighted heavily toward decisions by large institutional investors. BetterInvesting's individual members and investment clubs tend to have a longer-term focus than do institutions, with clubs' average holding period for stocks at 3.1 years in 2016, according to data. Holding quality stocks selling at reasonable prices for the long term allows clubs and individual investors to benefit from the return these stocks often earn when the market recognizes their excellence. Long-term investing also reduces the costs of trading, which effectively increases return. In December, the most common stocks acquired by investment clubs that subscribe to club-accounting portal myICLUB, in terms of number of clubs buying, were: BIXX includes companies of all sizes, from small and medium-size firms to the world's largest companies. To see the top 100 companies held by BetterInvesting members, go to the BetterInvesting website at . To track the performance of BIXX, go to the Solactive site: .   is a national nonprofit organization that has been empowering individual investors since 1951. Founded in Detroit, the association (formerly known as National Association of Investors Corporation) was borne of the conviction that anyone can become a successful long-term investor by following commonsense investing practices. has helped more than 5 million people become better, more informed investors by providing webinars, in-person events, easy-to-use online tools for analyzing stocks and mutual funds, a monthly magazine and a community of volunteers and like-minded investors. For more information about , visit its website at or call toll free (877) 275-6242.  ICLUBcentral Inc. develops powerful, commonsense tools for investment clubs and independent investors, including software products such as , the and stock research sites, the club accounting service, stock screen program and the and market-beating newsletters. ICLUBcentral, a wholly owned for-profit subsidiary of nonprofit investment education association , has remained true to BetterInvesting's fundamental investing principles while serving millions of individual investors striving for financial freedom. For more information, visit .   View original content: SOURCE  BetterInvesting Copyright (C) 2018 PR Newswire. All rights reserved Copyright \u00a9 2018 MarketWatch, Inc.  All rights reser